  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Look, here is the thing, this is only useful IF you are _only_ exposing the kube api to the end user. AND even then if you do not prevent mounting the host into containers via a PodSecurityPolicy then you could just exec in by combining the file descriptors....\r\n\r\nLike this window dressing of a feature is kinda un-useful and people are enabling it under circumstances where it is just plain stupid.... there is literally no point to this feature if you do not also have a pod security policy in place preventing people from mounting shit in to literally exec. Or if users have access to the nodes in the first place it makes literally no sense.\r\n",
